’Ł@2dad005d6cbdd37a290dfec0fc1d05d1077195067d345b153901f9aee665bc82Ł¬Title: title: export alias
Path: Examples
Content:
Alias ll to ls -l and export it from a module.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> module spam { export alias ll = ls -l }


```
